fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.processors
Class EmotionMLImporter

java.lang.Object
  fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.processors.EmotionMLProcessor
      fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.processors.EmotionMLImporter
Direct Known Subclasses:
JaxbEmotionMLImporter, JsonEmotionMLImporter
public class EmotionMLImporter
extends EmotionMLProcessor

A EmotionMLImporter imports EmotionML elements from the InputStream by first reading the stream as a DOM Element, then by validating the DOM Element with respect to the EmotionML standard and eventually by building EmotionML objects. It also offers different methods to import documents from other sources than stream. In order to read DOM Elements it uses an instance of an EmotionMLReader, which by default is a XMLEmotionMLReader. It is possible to setup a different reader.

Author:
Alexandre Denis
